In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims November 13-19, 2011, as American Education Week. He emphasizes the importance of education in ensuring the future economic prosperity and democracy of the United States. The President acknowledges the role schools play in nurturing students' academic interests and talents, and highlights the dedication of teachers and education professionals in guiding students towards their full potential. He calls for support for educators by strengthening schools, providing professional development opportunities, and recruiting top college graduates to become teachers. The President also recognizes the role of parents, community leaders, and mentors in instilling a love of learning in children. He emphasizes the need for education reform and creating high-performing classrooms to prepare future generations for success. The President urges all Americans to support their local schools during American Education Week and to create opportunities for every school and student in America.